main event: Two sightings of a round object flying from South to North were reported on 28 June 1956.
interesting points: The first sighting lasted 1.5 minutes and the second sighting lasted 2.5 to 3 minutes., The objects appeared round with a tapering back and were the size of a quarter at arm's length., The first object was all lit up, while the second had a light similar to an aircraft blinker light that blinked on and off about every 1.5 miles., Both objects emitted a flame and were dull against the sky., The report concludes that the sightings were probably caused by aircraft.
